on has several advantages:\n   - **Numerical Stability**: Multiplying probabilities can lead to very small numbers, causing underflow in computations. Log probabilities can help avoid this issue.\n   - **Additive Properties**: Instead of multiplying probabilities, you can add log probabilities, which simplifies calculations.\n\n### Example:\nIf a language model predicts that the token \"cats\" has a probability of 0.1 to follow \"I love,\" its log probability (using a natural log) is approximately -2.302 (since ln(0.1) = -2.302). A higher log probability (closer to 0) indicates a more likely token, while a lower log probability (more negative) indicates less likelihood.\n\n### Use in Language Models:\nToken log probabilities are useful in:\n- **Generating Text**: By sampling or selecting the next token based on its log probability.\n- **Evaluating Sequences**: Estimating the overall quality of generated text based on the cumulative log probabilities of the sequence of tokens.\n\nIn summary, token log probabilities provide a way to quantify the likelihood of word sequences in a manner that is computationally efficient and stable."}

